</p><p>Furthermore, adjusting the severity of chest trauma using TTSS and Ribscore by multivariable logistic regression analysis, we also evaluated the performance of the numbers of total and displaced rib fracture to predict the pulmonary complication. We found that three or more rib fractures or any displaced rib fracture was the most significant predictor for developing pulmonary complication (aOR: 5.49 95% CI: 1.82&#x02013;16.55, Table&#x000a0;<xref rid="Tab7" ref-type="table">7</xref>).<table-wrap id="Tab7"><label>Table 7</label><caption><p>Univariate and multivariate logistic regression analysis evaluating three or more total and any displaced rib fracture in predicting pulmonary complications</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th rowspan="2"/><th colspan="3">Univariable</th><th colspan="3">Multivariable</th></tr><tr><th>OR</th><th>CI</th><th>
